 Centane - Centane police arrested a 39-year-old man for possession of unlicensed firearm - a pistol. "The suspect was arrested on Thursday, during the early hours of the morniing, at Centule Village, Centane," said police spokesperson, Capt Jackson Manatha. "The firearm had one magazine with no rounds of ammunition. "The suspect will appear before the Centane Magistrate’s Court on Friday, on a charge of possession of unlicensed firearm." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 